Commentary.Commentary: So India have a lot of time to bat in this innings. They would look to make the most of it and take an unassailable lead in this innings and would like to make it the only innings they bat in. Bangladesh, on the other hand, would try to emulate the Indian bowlers. It won't be an easy task against this juggernaut of a batting side though. Can they restrict India or will India continue to steamroll them? Join us in a while to find out.

Hardly anything to talk about Bangladesh's batting. They won the toss but every batter struggled. Mushfiqur Rahim was the highest scorer but had India been at their usual self in the field, then that certainly would not have been the case. Liton and Mominul looked good but could not convert their starts. All-in-all the Bangla batsmen were completely decimated by the Indian bowlers and looked all over the place.

India have wrapped up Bangladesh for just 150. Brilliant bowling display from the hosts. They lost the toss but a look at this  innings will not make you feel like that. They were just too spicy and too good for the visitors to tackle. The only thing that can be criticized off this innings from the hosts would be their catching. Apart from that they were just so magnificent making Bangladesh work for every single run. The trio of Ashwin, Umesh and Ishant scalped two each whereas Shami had 3. Jadeja was wicket-less but in his defense he just bowled 3 overs.

OUT! BOWLED! That is the end of the innings! A brilliant delivery to end with from Umesh. He bowls a fullish delivery on off, Hossain looks to defend it but the ball goes past the outside edge and hits the top of off stump. The Indian bowlers have done a terrific job as they have BOWLED OUT BANGLADESH FOR JUST 150.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Hossain looks to guide this to the off side but misses it altogether.

Good length ball on off, Abu pushes it to cover and takes a couple. Jadeja gets across from point and tries to throw it to the keeper but does so poorly this time. The batters make it in this time. 150 up for the visitors.
Fullish delivery on the pads, Abu Jayed digs it out towards mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Abu defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Jayed defends it off the front foot to cover.
Beauty! But beats the edge and stumps once again. Good length ball on off, it zips away off the deck. Jayed looks to defend but misses.
Fuller outside off, it swings away. Abu hangs out his bat and the ball goes past the outside edge.
Fuller around off, Abu makes room and defends it in a typical tailenders fashion.
Short delivery on middle, Hossain defends it off the back foot.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Ebadot Hossain is the last man in.

OUT! RUN OUT! This time Taijul does not survive the throw from Jadeja. Islam flicks this good length ball on middle to deep backward square leg and wants a couple. Jadeja at runs to his right and gets to the ball quickly.  He send a good throw to the keeper and he whips the bails off. The umpire does not even go to the third umpire and gives it out immediately. The saying stands correct, never try to take an extra run of Ravindra Jadeja's arm.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! Good length ball on off, Jayed defends it to point and takes off for a single. Taijul, is late in getting off the blocks and Jadeja at point tries to put in a direct hit at the keeper's end. He misses and the ball rolls towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. Had Jadeja hit, Islam was well out. 5 runs added to the Bangladesh's score.
BEATEN! Umesh bowls a good length ball outside off, Abu makes room for himself towards the leg side to play it to the off side but misses it completely.
Starts with a good length ball on middle, Jayed defends it out to the off side.
Umesh Yadav is back on. 13-3-39-1, his figures so far.

BEATEN! Brilliant bowling this from Shami! Bowls a full delivery around off swinging into the batsman. Taijul looks to drive but does not account for the swing on it. He misses and the ball just whizzes past the off stump.
Good length ball on off, Taijul blocks it out.
Short ball down the leg side, Taijul looks to pull it but misses it. There is a stifled appeal for caught but nothing from the umpire.
On a length on middle, Islam defends it back to the bowler of the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Taijul drives this to cover for nothing.
Shami does not get the hat-trick! Bowls a good length delivery on off, Taijul defends it off the back foot to cover.
Mohammad Shami to bowl from the other end. This will be a hat-trick ball for Shami. Can he get it?
Full delivery on middle, Jayed does well to defend it.
Fullish delivery outside off, Abu plays it towards backward point and takes a couple before Rahane can run after it from gully and cut it off.
Ishant has to be cautious now. On the wicket delivery, he was given the final warning for running on the danger area. If he breaches the rule again he will not be allowed to bowl again in this match.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Jayed looks to guide this one but fails to put any bat on it.
BOUNCER! A nasty one at that! Ishant bowls it aimed at the body. Jayed does well to sway away from it.
On a length on off, Jayed defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Bangladesh are in deep, deep trouble here and nothing has gone their way apart from the toss. Yes, a few catches have been put down but the visitors have failed to make any use of it.
Abu Jayed is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a start to the session for the hosts. They have collected a team hat-trick. Ishant starts with a slightly full length ball outside off. Das, the only recognized batsman out there, looks to defend from within the crease but the ball goes off the outside edge towards Virat Kohli at first slip. He takes it by going down low. Ishant gets his second wicket of the innings.

We are back for the final session of the day! Liton Das and Taijul Islam make their way out to the middle. The Indians are also making their way out to the middle. Ishant Sharma will bowl the first over after Tea.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Bangladesh were good at the start of this session but will be disappointed as they could not make the most of it. They lost the plot completely after Mominul's wicket. Mahmudullah struggled, Liton though has looked good, the worrying sign is he will have to take the mantle here as Mushfiqur and Mehidy also got dismissed right at the end of the session. Can Liton Das find some support and manage to see off the day or will India continue to stamp their authority? Join us after the break to find out.

What an end to the session for India! Mohammed Shami two-in-two wickets has ensured that when the hosts come back for the final session of the day, they are into the visitors tail. Bangladesh had started well after Lunch scoring runs at a brisk pace. They were also helped by some poor catching in the field by the Indians. But then, Mominul Haque was castled by Ashwin and that opened the floodgates. Ravichandran Ashwin added one more wicket to his kitty before Shami came back on to pick out 2 more wickets right at the stroke of Tea.

OUT! LBW! Two-in-two for Shami and he is now on a hat-trick. He will have to wait though as it is also Tea on Day 1. Pacy full ball on off, there is reverse swing on this one. No batsman likes it first up, Mehidy is an unlucky man as he gets this jaffa first up. He looks to play but misses. The ball hits flush on his front pad. The Indian players put in a loud, confident appeal and the umpire is in agreement with him. Mehidy looks at his partner and tries to contact with Liton but Das was busy looking somewhere else. The timer goes to off and Mehidy departs for a golden duck. How unlucky is Mehidy Hasan? Ball Tracker later on rolls in and shows that had Mehidy taken the review he would have survived as the ball was going onto miss the leg pole.
Mehidy Hasan replaces Mushfiqur Rahim out in the middle.

OUT! Bowled! This is pace bowling at his best! This is a beauty of a delivery. Three outswingers and now the inswinger. Good length ball around off, it comes in venomously. Mushfiqur looks to defend but the ball goes right through the gate of bat and pad. It goes on top of off. A pace bowler's delight. Rahim just looks at the pitch in awe. He cannot do anything off that as this was a ball sent by the pace bowling gods.
Good length ball outside off, Mushi leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Rahim leaves it alone.
Full and swinging away. Mushfiqur lunges forward and leaves it alone.
On middle and leg, Mushfiqur flicks it to the on side.
Another gem! Good length ball outside off, it comes in a lot off the deck. Liton leaves it alone and the ball just about misses the off pole.
Full outside off, Das drives it to the right of mid off. It comes off the inner half of his bat. Ashwin dives to his right and saves runs for his side.
Length ball on off, Das defends it off the front foot.
Length ball outside off, Liton punches it to point.
On the pads, Rahim looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pad and they steal a leg bye.
Beauty! Ishant has bowled some gems today. Good length ball outside off, it zips in off the deck. Mushfiqur is aware of his stumps and offers a good leave.
Ishant Sharma is back on. 10-5-18-1 are his figures so far.

Uppish but safe. Full outside off, Das looks to drive it on the up. He does not time it well and it goes uppishly to the left of the fielder at point. Ashwin there dives on that side and saves runs for his team. No chance of catching that as the ball had fallen short.
Bouncer! Das sees it coming and ducks under it.
On the pads, Das glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.

FOUR! Good ball but the shot is an even better one. Full and swinging in. Das gets on his front foot and just drives it with ease off the middle of his bat through mid off for a boundary. Liton has so far looked the most at ease on this pitch today.
Full and swinging away. Das plays it with the swing towards cover.
Shami comes back and makes the ball move. Good length ball outside off, it moves away. Liton does not tease that one.
Mohammed Shami comes back into the attack. His figures read 9-2-21-1 so far.
Tossed up on off, Mushfiqur bends his back and defends the ball onto the ground.
Flighted on off, Mushfiqur defends it off the front foot.
Around the pads, Das flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Tossed up on off, Das pushes it to cover.
Jadeja targets the stumps, Das lunges forward and blocks it.
Flatter on off and middle, Liton defends it off the back foot.
Shorter on off, Mushi blocks it off the front foot.
On the pads, Das turns it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Tossed up on off, Liton defends it off the front foot.
Floated on middle and off, Rahim milks it to long on for one.
Floated on off, Rahim turns it to the on side.
Tossed up on the stumps, Rahim keeps it out.
Yorker from Jaddu. It is on off, Liton keeps it out.
FOUR! Aggressive shot. A rare full toss from Jadeja on off, Liton smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Das keeps it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Beauty of a delivery this. Quicker and turning away, Liton looks to defend but the ball spins and takes the outside edge and kisses the pad. It goes between Saha and first slip onto the fence. Jadeja appealed for LBW but the umpire signals it as a boundary. Kohli does not take the review.
Floated on off and middle, Das keeps it out.
Jaddu bowls it flatter on middle, Liton taps it back to the bowler.
Flat delivery outside off, Rahim plays the square cut towards point for nothing.
Another full delivery on middle, Liton works it to long on and takes another single. Ashwin tries to stop it with a dive but fails to do so.
Floated ball outside off, Liton pushes it to mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, Das defends it back to the bowler.
Flat delivery outside off, Rahim guides this to third man and crosses over for a single.
Floated ball on off, Rahim defends it to point.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Mushfiqur flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Loopy ball on off, Rahim defends it out.
Flatter delivery on middle, Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Fires this one on middle and leg, Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Starts with a full delivery on middle, Mushfiqur flicks it to mid-wicket.
Ravindra Jadeja is finally brought into the attack.
On the pads, Das turns it to the on side.
Shorter on off, Das looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated on off, Das keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Das strokes it to mid on.

FOUR! Liton is off the mark in style. This will give the Bangladesh's dressing room a lot of confidence. Flighted on off, Das gets on his front foot and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Liton Das is the new man in.

OUT! BOWLED! Mahmudullah's struggling innings comes to an end. Ashwin has not had a lot of help from his slip fielders so he has decided to do the damage all by himself here. Straighter one on off, Mahmudullah looks to sweep but misses the straighter one completely. He gets too far across and the ball goes onto hit the off pole. Bangladesh in trouble here as half their side are back in the hut.
Another good length ball on middle, Mushfiqur defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, defended back to the bowler by Rahim.
Full delivery on middle, Rahim works it off his pads towards deep square leg and takes a couple.
Good length ball on the pads, Mahmudullah works it to fine leg and gives Mushfiqur the strike.
On a length on off, Rahim pushes it to point and takes another single.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Mahmudullah flicks it to mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
Flighted on off, Rahim looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes towards cover.
Flighted on off, Mushfiqur keeps it out.
Floated on middle and off, Mahmudullah nudges it to long on for one.

Dropped! This is a genuine sitter and Rahane is having a torrid time here at slips. Excellent ball from Ashwin. Gives this air and draws the batsman forward. Mahmudullah lunges forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball kisses the thigh pad of Saha and goes to the left of Rahane at first slip. He gets his hand to it but the ball just won't stick and it comes out yet again. Third catch dropped by Rahane, very seldom you see this from Kohli's Test deputy. India have been sub-par in the field today. Mahmudullah has not had the best of starts here but he is getting his chances here and needs to make them count.
Tossed up on off, Mahmudullah defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Mushfiqur flicks it wide of the diving mid on fielder and gets a single.
Fuller on off, Mahmudullah looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards mid off. Another exciting over comes to an end.
Beauty! Fuller around off, it pitches and moves away. Mahmudullah looks to defend but his feet go nowhere near the ball and he gets squared up. Lucky not to edge it behind.
Length ball outside off, Mahmudullah looks a bit unsettled out in the middle. He slashes hard at it but misses.
Yorker. A good one, Mahmudullah pushes it to the left of mid on.
Back of a length ball around off, Mahmudullah hops up and keeps it down towards point.
Good length ball around off, Mushfiqur strokes it to point and shouts for a single. Mahmudullah responds and they take it.
Off spinner on off, Mahmudullah flicks it to square leg.
Another beauty! Flatter and slightly quicker outside off, Mahmudullah looks to defend but gets beaten all ends up.
Floated on off, Mushfiqur milks it to long on and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off and middle, Rahim turns it to the on side.
Tossed up on off, Rahim pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter around off, Mushfiqur dabs it wide of first slip.

Drinks Break! A hour which has gone both ways. Bangladesh started well after Lunch getting some quick runs but they would be disappointed with the wicket of Mominul Haque just at the stroke of Drinks. Mushfiqur Rahim is going strong for them at one end and he would look for a big score here. India, on the other hand, still remain ahead in the game and they would look to pick up further wickets. Ashwin and Ishant have bowled well but have not been able to find the edges.
Mohammed Shami is seen going out of the ground for some reason. Shubman Gill replaces him on the field.
FOUR! Pulled and with authority! Back of a length ball on off, Mahmudullah gets on his back foot and pulls it with power through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller on middle, Mahmudullah flicks it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Fuller on off, Mahmudullah defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Mahmudullah keeps it out.
Another one which is defended by Mahmudullah on his back foot.
Good length ball on off, Mahmudullah defends it off his back foot.
Umesh Yadav is back on. 10-3-27-1 are his figures so far.
Flighted on off, Rahim pushes it to point.
Shorter on off, Mushfiqur blocks it.
On the pads, Rahim turns it to square leg.
Floated outside off, Rahim plays it to point.

DROPPED! Tough chance but one has to say lady luck is going Mushfiqur's way! Short and quicker around off. It turns in sharply. Rahim looks to defend with a slant bat but the ball  kisses his glove and goes to the keeper sharply at an awkward height. It hits Saha on his pad and lobs away. He cannot hold onto it. Ashwin knows that it is a very difficult chance and hence no big disappointment from him.
Floated on off, Rahim keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Mahmudullah tucks it to the on side. End of an exciting over from Ishant.
Fuller on middle, Mahmudullah flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Mahmudullah looks to keep it out but gets an inside edge onto his pads. No harm done though.

Good length ball on middle and off, Mahmdullah looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him high on his pad. There is a confident appeal but umpire Erasmus says no. The Indians think about the review but Kohli thinks it is too high and they do not review it. The Ball Tracker later on shows that the Indian skipper was indeed right as it would have gone onto miss the stumps.
Back of a length ball on off, Mahmudullah defends it off the front foot.
Bouncer! A well directed one. Mahmudullah ducks under it.

Ambitious and risky from Mahmudullah. Tossed up on off, Mahmudullah comes down the track and flicks it uppishly off his inner half of his bat towards deep mid-wicket for a single. He keeps the strike and that run also brings up the 100 for Bangladesh.
Shorter on off, Mahmudullah defends it off the back foot.
Another one around the pads, Mahmudullah cannot go past the fielder with his flick.
Tossed up on middle, Mahmudullah flicks it to square leg.
Floated on off, Mahmudullah defends it off the front foot.
Mahmudullah replaces his skipper out in the middle.

OUT! Bowled! Ashwin strikes. Fourth wicket and the fourth bowler to get it. A terrible leave this from the skipper. He won't look at this fondly. The budding stand has been broken by Ashwin. How many times have we seen that? Floated on off, Mominul thinks this one would spin away and leaves it alone. The ball though straightens after pitching and goes onto hit the off pole. A slight lapse of concentration from the Bangladesh skipper has brought his downfall. He will be gutted with it. This is the 250th home  scalp for India's new spin king, Ravichandran Ashwin.
Full again to end the over. Another inswinger on middle and off, Rahim flicks it to mid-wicket.
Almost tempts Rahim. Full outside off, asking Mushfiqur to drive. He almost goes for it but pulls out at the last moment.
Length ball outside off, Mushfiqur shoulders arms to it.
Full on off and middle, Rahim pushes it to mid on.

Inside edge saves Rahim. Full on off, there is a hint of inswing. Rahim looks to flick but it goes off the inner half of his bat onto the pads. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Fuller on off, Mominul defends it towards point off the outer half of his bat and gets a single.
Follows the boundary with calm and easy flick.

FOUR! Excellently played. He played this shot in the first T20I at critical junctures and he has played it well here as well. Floated on off and middle, Rahim premeditates his paddle sweep and executes it well fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Mushfiqur nudges it to mid on.
Shorter on off, Rahim turns it to short leg.
Floated on off, Mushfiqur defends it off the back foot.
Ashwin gives this air and bowls it full outside off, Mominul strokes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Haque flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Poor ball this from Ishant! Full delivery on the pads and this is easy pickings for Mominul. He just flicks it away through the square leg region and picks up another boundary.
Full delivery outside off, Haque shoulders arms to this one.
PLAY AND A MISS! This is top class stuff! Ishant bowls it full outside off swinging away, Haque attempts to defend yet again but the ball goes past the outside edge.
On a length outside off, Haque lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Ishant returns  with a beautiful delivery! Sharma bowls it on a length on off which moves away, Mominul looks to defend from the crease but misses it altogether.
Ishant Sharma is on for the first time in this session. 7-4-12-1, his figures so far.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahim flicks it to mid-wicket for nothing.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flatter delivery on middle, Rahim defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Wow! Rahim follows the six with a boundary. Ashwin overcorrects his length and goes short outside off, Rahim stands back and cuts it through backward point for another boundary.

SIX! Beautiful use of the feet from Rahim! Ashwin bowls a flighted delivery on middle, Mushfiqur comes down the track and plays it over the bowler's head for the first maximum of the game. 50-run stand comes up between these two. They need to carry on though as the job is not even half done here.
Flighted ball on middle, Rahim flicks it to short fine leg.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on middle, Haque flicks it through the deep square leg region and takes a boundary.

BEATEN! Another piece of brilliant bowling from Shami! Mohammed bowls a fullish delivery leaving the batsman a bit, Mominul attempts to defend it but the ball goes past the outside edge and into the keeper's mitts.
Good length ball on middle, Rahim flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, Rahim drives it to cover for nothing.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled by Shami! Good length ball outside off swinging away a touch, Rahim looks to defend from within the crease but misses the ball completely.
Good length ball on middle, Rahim defends it out onto the pitch.
Tossed up ball outside off, Haque drives it to cover for another dot.
Flat delivery on off, Mominul defends it to point.
Loopy ball on off, Mominul drives it towards mid on.
Floated ball on middle, Rahim comes down the track and flicks it to square leg for a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Rahim camps on his back foot and defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Mushfiqur flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Mushfiqur defends it off the back foot towards point and calls Mominul for a quick single.
Good length ball way outside off, Mushfiqur shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Mominul flicks it to fine leg and takes a single. Ravindra Jadeja comes across and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
Full delivery on off, Rahim drives it to cover and takes off for a single.
On a length on middle, Rahim flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball swinging away from the batsman. Mushfiqur plays it inside the line and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Floated ball on off, Rahim looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge of the bat towards fine leg. The batters take a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Floated ball around off, Haque drives this towards cover and takes a single.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Mominul flicks it to mid-wicket. No run.
Flatter delivery on middle, Mominul flicks it towards square leg for nothing.
Flighted delivery on off, Mominul drives it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Rahim leaves it alone.
Shami misses his line and sprays one down the leg side. Mushfiqur looks to flick but misses.
Outside off, Mushfiqur leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Mushfiqur pushes it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Rahim leaves it alone.
Full around off, Mominul drives it to the right of mid off. Ashwin there dives to that side but misfields allowing them to take a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Rahim defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Flatter delivery outside off, Mushfiqur plays a square cut but straight to point.
Floated ball on off, Mominul drives it to cover and takes a single.
Flighted ball outside off, Rahim pushes it to point and takes a single.

DROPPED! Rahane puts down an easy chance! Mushfiqur gets another life in this innings! This though is beautifully bowled by Ashwin! Flighted ball outside off, Mushfiqur looks to defend it off the back foot but it goes off the outside edge at an awkward height to Rahane at first slip. Ajinkya is slow in getting his hands to it and it lobs off his chest and into the ground. Another big miss from India. Second drop for Rahane in this innings.
Ravichandran Ashwin to partner Shami from the other end to start the session. 4-0-11-0, his figures in the first session.
On a length in the channel, Mominul looks to drive it from te crease but it goes off the inside half of the bat. The ball goes mid off for nothing.
Full delivery around off, Mominul drives this nicely but finds the fielder at cover.
Good length delivery outside off, Haque lets the ball go to the keeper.
LEG BYE! On a length on middle and leg, Mushfiqur looks to flick it but it goes off his pads towards fine leg for a leg bye.
On a length on off, Rahim defends it to point off the back foot.
Starts with a full delivery swinging away, Mushfiqur lunges forward and pushes it to point. Jadeja comes across and cleans it up.

We are back for the second session! Mushfiqur Rahim and the skipper stride out to the middle to resume their innings. The Indians, led by Virat Kohli, also make their way out to the field. Mohammed Shami will start after the break.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

So another session in the Indian shores dominated by Virat Kohli and Co. Can the Bangla Tigers roar back and enjoy a better second session or will India continue their dominance? Join us after the break to find out.

After winning the toss and opting to bat, Bangladesh struggled to get going. Both their openers, Shadman and Kayes, struggled in the middle but it looked like they would somehow manage to survive the danger phase but that was not to be as Umesh and Ishant sent both the openers back to the pavilion. Mithun and Mominul then tried to steady the ship but the former could not last long. Rahim joined his skipper and though he has ridden his luck, he has managed to take his side to Lunch without any more casualties. The skipper has looked good and Bangladesh will be hoping that these two can build on their 32-run stand post Lunch and take the visitors to a good total.

No doubt to whom this session belonged to! The Indians have been in top gear and this session was an exhibition of how good their pace bowling attack is. All three pacers have bowled with venom and passion and their good work has been rewarded with one wicket each. Umesh and Ishant were excellent at the start while Shami and Ashwin too were good, not giving away any free runs.
Short ball outside off, Haque rocks on his back foot and punches this to backward square leg for nothing. With that, it is LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Full delivery outside off, Mominul lets the ball go the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Umesh! Good length ball outside off, Mominul attempts to play at it from inside the crease but fails to put any bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Mominul lets the ball go to the keeper.
On a length on middle, Rahim flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Beautifully played from Rahim! Short delivery outside off, Rahim camps on his back foot and punches it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Another brilliant delivery. Full and swinging in. Rahim looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller around the off pole, Mushi defends it towards point.
Outside off and once again Rahim leaves it alone.
Fuller outside off, Mushfiqur leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! This is brilliant bowling but Mushfiqur rides his luck here. Good length ball outside off, it jags back in viciously. Rahim looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps and fine down the leg side for a boundary. This ball deserved a wicket and these are the balls that sometimes make you feel for the bowlers.
Good length ball on  off, Rahim defends it with authority.
EDGY FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Mominul looks to drive it from inside the crease. The ball takes the outside edge of the bat and the ball flies over third slip for a boundary.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball down the leg side, Haque looks to flick it but misses the ball.
Good length delivery on middle, Rahim flicks it towards the square leg region for a single.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Mushfiqur looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads. The Indians put in a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.

DROPPED! How has Kohli dropped this? He should have done a lot better there. Mushfiqur is a good player and he might hurt the Indians. Good length ball around off, Rahim looks to  push at it away from the body. Mushfiqur checks his shot at the last moment but it goes off the outside edge towards Virat Kohli at third slip. He dives to his right and makes a mess of it. Rahim should have left this ball alone.
BEATEN! Good length ball around off, Mominul looks to defend but misses it completely.
On a length on off, Rahim defends it off the front foot towards cover and calls Mominul for a single.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Rahim attempts to defend it but fails to make any connection to it.
Full delivery on middle, Rahim drives it back to the bowler. Ishant has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Rahim shoulders arms to this one.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Mushfiqur looks to defend but misses it. The ball goes on to hit the back thigh pad. The Indians appeal but the umpire shakes his head. They opt against the review. The replays show that it was clipping the top of leg stump. Rahim wanted the single but is sent back by his skipper.
Ishant Sharma replaces Ashwin. So change from both the ends. 6 runs and a wicket off his first.
Full delivery on middle, Mominul drives it to mid on for nothing.
BOUNCER! Umesh bowls it aimed at the body of Mominul who ducks under it.
FOUR! Another one in the same region! Umesh Yadav bowls a good length ball outside off, Mominul opens the face of the bat yet again and plays it to third man for the second boundary of the over.
FOUR! Nicely played! Umesh bows it on a length around off, Haque opens the face of the bat and guides this towards the third man region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Haque plays it inside the line and lets the ball go the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Mushfiqur looks to defend but does so with soft hands. The ball goes past the diving Rahane at gully and towards short third man. The batters take a single.
Umesh Yadav is back on. 7-3-8-1, his figures so far.
FOUR! Floated delivery on the pads, Haque plays a delicate flick shot towards fine leg for a boundary. If there was a leg slip there, the ball might have gone straight to hand.
Flatter delivery outside off, Mominul guides it to point.
Loopy ball on off, Mominul defends it towards the point region.
Floated ball on middle, Mominul defends it off the front foot.
Flighted ball on off, Mominul drives it to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Rahim pushes it to mid on and calls Mominul for a quick single. He gets off the mark with that one.
Good length ball on middle, Haque defends it out to the leg side.
Another good length swinging a bit but not enough to make Mominul play. He leaves the ball alone yet again.
Good length ball outside off, Haque shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle, Mominul looks to defend but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards the leg side for nothing.
BOUNCER! WIDE! Shami bowls this way over the head of Mominul who ducks under it. It is wide.
On a length in the channel, Haque lunges forward and blocks it to point.
Good length ball on off, Mominul defends it towards point.
Shorter again on off, Mushfiqur defends if off his back foot.
Slightly shorter on off, Rahim punches it but this time finds point.
Gives this air on off and middle, Mushfiqur flicks it but straight to the man at short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Mushfiqur starts his innings with a calm front foot defense.
Flighted around off, Haque drives it to cover and gets one.
Floated on the stumps, Mominul keeps it out.
Mushfiqur Rahim is the new man in.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb and Mithun has to make the long walk back to the pavilion. Bangladesh slip further. Shami bowls a full delivery on middle swinging into the batsman, Mithun looks to flick it but fails to read the line of the ball. The ball goes onto hit the pads of Mithun. Shami appeals and the umpire gives it out immediately. Both the batsmen are now having a chat to discuss the review but decide against it. Good decision in the end as the replays show that the ball was going on to hit the middle stump. Mominul's decision to bat first is backfiring at the moment.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on  off, Mithun looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards third man and into the fence for a boundary.
BEATEN! Brilliant stuff from Shami! Bowls it on a length outside off, Mithun looks to poke at it but fails to make any connection to it.
Good length ball outside off, Mithun defends it to point.

Good length ball on off, Mominul defends it towards point and looks for the single. Jadeja throws it to the bowler's end and hits. The batsman gets his bat inside the crease on time and the ball goes towards long off allowing the batsmen to take a couple.
Flatter delivery outside off, Haque lets the ball go to the keeper.
On middle, Haque defends it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

DROPPED! Rahane is the culprit! It is  a tough chance though for Ajinkya! Flatter delivery outside off, Mominul looks to cut it but it goes off the outside edge towards Rahane at first slip. He dives to his right and tries to pouch it with one hand but fails to hold onto it. The ball rolls towards third man and the batters take a couple. Rohit has a shy the bowler's end and hits but Mominul was well in.
Flatter delivery on off, Mithun looks to defend but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards the square leg region. The batters take a single.
Flighted ball on the pads, Mithun works it to mid on.
Another good length ball coming into the batsman, Mominul leaves it alone. Another good over from Shami comes to an end.
Good length ball swinging into the batsmen, Mominul once again shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Haque lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Mominul defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Haque does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Mominul shoulders arms to this one.
Change of ends for Mohammed Shami.
Flighted ball on middle, Mithun defends it out. 2 runs have come off the first over from Ashwin.
Tosses this ball up on middle, Mithun drives this back to the bowler.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Flighted delivery outside off, Mithun drives it towards the cover region and takes a couple before the fielder can cut it off.
Full delivery on middle, Mithun flicks it towards the leg side for no run.
Flatter delivery on middle, Mithun defends it off the back foot.
Spin time. Ravichandran Ashwin is into the attack.

NOT OUT! It has hit the pad first but it is umpire's call on impact! Umesh bowls an inswinger on off which swings a touch. Mithun looks to work it on the leg side but is wrapped on the back pad. It seems as if it was bat but Umesh convinces his skipper to go for the review. Virat obliges and signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows that there was an inside edge but it was after the ball had kisses the back pad as the Ultra Edge shows a spike as it goes past the back pad.. The T.V umpire after having a couple of looks rolls in the Ball Tracker. It shows that the impact was umpire's call though the pitching was on line and the ball would have hit the stumps. India don't get the wicket but also don't lose the review.
Review time! Umesh Yadav has a word with his skipper and convinces Kohli to take the review. It looks to be taking the inside edge to the naked eye. Let's see what the replays have to say.
On middle, defended off the front foot towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on off, Mithun guides it to gully.
BEATEN! Umesh is on fire at the moment! Yadav bowls an outswinger around off, Mithun looks for a drive but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length outside off, Mithun guides it to gully where the fielder dives to stop the ball.

BEATEN! Brilliant bowling this from Umesh! Good length ball swinging away from the batsmen, Mithun attempts to defend but luckily for him, the ball passes the outside edge of the bat and into the keeper's gloves.

Drinks! It has been a brilliant hour of play for the Indians. Their seamers have bowled extremely well, beating the edges of the bat at the start. They were rewarded though with the wickets of the Bangladeshi openers and are looking really good here. The Bangla Tigers have not looked comfortable at the crease after choosing to bat first and will need their skipper to play a long innings to get them on track to a good score. The pair of Mithun and Mominul have taken their time and look a bit settled now. Can they stay out in the middle at least till Lunch and solidfy the ship.
Length ball outside off, Mominul leaves it alone.
Full on off, Haque defends it off the front foot.

Super stop from the flying Rahane at gully. Full outside off, Mominul drives it to the left of gully. Rahane dives on that side and saves a certain boundary. Superb work from the Indian Test vice captain.
Full outside off, Mominul leaves it alone.
Very full and swinging away. Mithun guides it with the swing to the right of point and takes a single.
Ripper. Good length ball around off, Mithun looks to defend but the ball straightens and squares him up completely.
Full on off and middle, Mominul flicks it stylishly but straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Well, Umesh has changed his side because he has been warned for running on the danger area of the pitch.
Outside off, left alone.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it on a length outside off. It comes in with the angle but Mominul leaves it alone.
Way outside off, Mominul does not fall in the trap to go for the drive.
Good length ball outside off, Mominul leaves it alone.
Good length ball on top of middle, Mithun looks to defend but the ball goes to square leg off the inner half of his bat for a single.
Umesh Yadav to carry on from this end.
Fuller outside off, it comes in but it is too full to come in and trouble Mominul. He leaves it alone. Good carry to the keeper as it goes to Saha around head high.
Full around off, Mominul defends it to cover.
Shami steams in and hits the deck hard on middle and off, Haque defends it off the lower half of his bat. The ball hits his pad and stays around the crease.
On the pads, Mominul glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Comes over the wicket now. It is on a length on top of off, Mithun pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets off the mark as well.
Shami starts with a length ball on the pads coming around the wicket. Mominul glances it to the on side and gets off the mark with a single.
Mohammed Shami replaces Ishant Sharma.
Fuller on off, MM pushes it back to the bowler. This could be the end of the opening bowlers' first spell.
Fuller on off, Mithun looks to defend but edges it to the man at gully slip on the bounce.
On a good length area outside off, Mithun looks to punish that as he goes for the punch but he ends up under edging it to the keeper on a bounce.
Good length ball on off, Mithun blocks it off his back foot.
Length ball on off, Mithun looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge. He played it with soft hands and hence it goes to the man on the bounce to gully.
Good length ball outside off, Mithun leaves it alone.
Full and swinging in on middle and off. Mithun looks to flick but it goes off his pad behind square on the leg side for a leg bye.
Full and going away. Mithun gets on his front foot and pushes it to mid off.
Fuller outside off, no swing on this one. Mithun is not tempted to go for the drive and he leaves it alone.
Another length ball which comes in, Mithun shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball way outside off, Mithun sways away from it.

Another gorgeous delivery. Good length ball outside off, it comes in a lot. Mithun leaves it alone and the ball just about misses the stumps. As the saying goes as long as the leave misses the stumps it is a good leave.
Left alone once again. Mominul is ready to play the waiting game as he once again leaves it alone.
Another solid leave from the Bangla skipper.
Nice leave. Good length ball around off, Haque keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Haque shoulders arms to it.
On top of the stumps, Mominul leaves it alone.
Outside off, Mominul starts his innings with a confident leave.
Mohammad Mithun walks out to the middle.

OUT! Caught! Both the openers are back for early showers. This is not the best of balls from Ishant in this spell but all the pressure from the good deliveries has seen him get this wicket. Both the opening bowlers have a wicket to their name and rightfully so. Full and outside off, Shadman looks to go for the glorious shot. He goes for a big drive but the ball moves away just a bit, not much. It does enough to take the outside edge of Shadman's bat and straight into the mitts of Saha. They appeal and the umpire raises his finger and gives Islam his marching orders.
Fuller than the previous one on off, Shadman once again defends it confidently.
Ishant hits the deck hard and makes the ball come in. Shadman has his body behind his bat and blocks it.
Back of a length on off, Islam blocks it.
Fuller on off, SI keeps it out.
Targets the stumps, Shadman defends it.
Mominul Haque is the new man in.

OUT! Caught! India finally draw the first blood. It has been coming but it has come after Kayes had found some confidence. Umesh has the last laugh. This is a strong comeback from Yadav after being hit for a boundary. Good length ball around off, it is in the channel of uncertainty. Kayes looks to defend but the ball shapes away and finds the outside edge of Imrul's bat. The ball goes uppishly to the left of gully. One with the safest pair of hands, Ajinkya Rahane moves to that side and takes a comfortable catch. It has been an excellent start by the hosts and now they have a wicket to show for it as well.
A confident leave. See what a boundary does. Good length ball outside off, Kayes lunges forward and leaves it alone stylishly.

FOUR! Poor ball and the first boundary from the middle of the bat. This will build Kayes' confidence. Full and wide outside off, Kayes gets on his front foot and slams it through point for a boundary.
Another brilliant ball. Good length ball on off, Kayes looks to defend but the ball zips past him and goes past his outside edge.
On the pads, Kayes tucks it to square leg.
Play and a miss again. Bangladesh are surviving but don't know how. Good length ball on off, Kayes looks to defend but once again gets beaten by the movement.
Good length ball on off, Islam defends it off the front foot.

Another quick single. A direct hit here would have put Islam in trouble. Fuller on off, Kayes defends it with soft hands and is called for a quick run. He responds. Ishant gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end but his throw is a wild one. Luckily for India, it costs no extra run.
Good length ball outside off, Kayes looks to defend but gets squared up once again.

Direct hit but safely in. Shadman smartly follows the boundary with a quick single. Good length ball on off, Shadman defends it off his front foot with soft hands and gets on his bike. Shami gets to the ball quickly and scores a direct hit at the keeper's end. Luckily for the visitors, Kayes is in.

FOUR! Streaky! Full outside off, Shadman slashes at it. He does not get to the pitch of it. The ball takes the thick outside edge as it moves away late. It goes wide of the man at gully for a boundary. First one of the day. It is a waiting game for Ishant as well and he won't mind that.
Another play and a miss. Good length ball outside off, Shadman looks to play but once again gets beaten. Something has to give now.
Good ball to end the over. Good length ball outside off, Kayes looks to play at it but misses. First over with runs in it.
On the stumps, Kayes defends it off his front foot.
Shadman is off the mark now. Fuller on off, Islam pushes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Another screamer. Good length ball outside off, Shadman initially looks to play at it but the ball moves in and Islam ends up leaving it with his bat covering the stumps.
Bangladesh are finally off the mark. Fuller on leg and middle, Kayes looks to flick but does so off the inner half of his bat towards fine leg for a single.

Ishant is making it go away from around the wicket and Umesh is making it come in from over the wicket here. Good length ball on middle and leg, Kayes looks to defend but the ball comes in and hits him on his thigh pad.
Play and a miss! Full outside off, Shadman throws his bat at it for a wild drive and misses. Ohhzz and ahhzz from the fielders standing behind the stumps.
Absolute beauty! Ishant bowls fuller outside off, it pitches and goes against the angle once again. Shadman looks to defend but once again is beaten.
Ohh!! The radar starting to work for Ishant now. Full outside off, Shadman looks to defend but the ball moves away beating the outside edge of Islam's bat.
Joel Wilson was supposed to umpire in this game but he is sick and Rod Tucker has replaced him.
Nicely bowled. Good length ball outside off, it shapes away from the southpaw. Shadman shoulders arms to it.
This should give Shadman some confidence. Full on off, Islam gets on his front foot and drives it right off the meat of the bat but straight to the man at mid off.

Still no run! Slightly fuller on off, Shadman looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes off the outside edge to the left of gully. The fielder there dives on that side and keeps Bangladesh's score to zero.
Good length ball outside off, Kayes looks for the drive but fails to put any bat on it. Umesh, just like Ishant, starts off with a maiden.
On a length on middle, Kayes flicks it but uppishly. It falls just short of the short leg fielder.
Good length ball down the leg side, Kayes looks to flick it but misses it. Nice carry to Saha behind the stumps.
On a length on middle, Imrul looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. No run.
Good length ball on middle, Kayes flicks it towards the leg side for nothing.
BEATEN! Excellent start from Umesh! On a length on middle which swings in a bit. Imrul looks to defend but the ball cuts him in half and the ball goes to the keeper.
Umesh Yadav to partner Ishant Sharma from the other end.
Another good length ball outside off, Shadman leaves this ball alone to the keeper. Maiden over to begin with from Ishant.
On a length outside off, Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Another good length ball in the channel outside off, Shadman lets the ball go to the keeper.
Ishant comes around the wicket this time and bowls it full outside off, Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Shadman shoulders arms to this one.
Starts with a good length ball outside off which swings away a lot. Shadman leaves it alone to the keeper.

Done and dusted with the anthems and now its time for the action to begin! Shadman Islam and Imrul Kayes make their way out to the middle to open the innings for Bangladesh. The Indian players led by Virat Kohli take on to the field and take their respective position in the field. Ishant Sharma to start the proceedings for the hosts with the new ball. Shadman to take the strike.
Time for the national anthems. The players from both sides are out in the centre. We are not far away from the start.
Bangladesh (PLAYING XI) - Imrul Kayes, Shadman Islam, Mohammad Mithun, Mominul Haque (C), Mushfiqur Rahim, Mahmudullah, Liton Das (WK), Mehidy Hasan, Taijul Islam, Abu Jayed, Ebadat Hossain.

India (PLAYING XI) - Mayank Agarwal, Rohit Sharma, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Ravindra Jadeja, Wriddhiman Saha (WK), Ravichandran Ashwin, Umesh Yadav, Mohammed Shami, Ishant Sharma.

Indian skipper, Virat Kohli says that the pitch has a bit of grass on it and adds that historically it is suited to bowl first. Further adds that they are playing 3 seamers and this will help them. Tells they wanted to bowl first and feels the best part to bat on here will be after the first session on Day 2. Further tells they are playing 2 spinners so they are covered for the third innings as well. On his team changes, Virat informs that Shahbaz Nadeem is not a part of the squad and Ishant Sharma has replaced him.

Bangladesh skipper, Mominul Haque says that it looks a good pitch for batting and hence the decision. Further says that the pitch will do something in the fourth innings. Adds that it's an honour for him to lead his country. Tells that they are playing with seven batsmen and four bowlers.
Toss - The two captains are out in the middle for the toss. Up goes the coin and it comes down in Bangladesh's favour.  They choose to bat first.

Pitch report -  Murali Kartik is down for the pitch report. He says that it is a red soil wicket.  He is then joined by Sunil Gavaskar who says that it is a very good surface. Further adds that the new-ball bowlers will enjoy bowling here. Adds that the pitch will get slower but not from Day 1. Mentions that there is a bit of moisture and it will assist the seamers early on. Further goes on to say that the team winning the toss will look to bat first.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of the first Test between India and Bangladesh. The Bangla tigers are facing a tough challenge against a very good Indian side. Under a new captain, Mominul Haque, the visitors would hope for a good performance in order to have any chance to beat this strong Indian side. They are without their key players as Tamim Iqbal ruled himself out while Shakib Al Hasan has been banned from all forms of cricket. Although, the odds are heavily in favour of the hosts, the Bangla Tigers are capable of putting in a surprise. India, on the other hand, have been dominant in the ICC Test championship so far beating the West Indies and the Proteas in their previous assignments. They have never lost a Test match to Bangladesh and would hope to continue that run in this series as well. Their bowling has worked wonders and is in red-hot form at the  moment. Will the Bangla Tigers spring in a surprise or will the hosts continue to dominate? Toss and team updates in a while.
They have 3 days to bat and against this formidable bowling line-up, if they manage to do it then this Bangladesh side will go down in history. Can they do it? Join us in a while to find out.

So the inevitable has happened. India's final flurry on Day 2 means that they will not bat again as they declared overnight. Bangladesh have a mammoth task in their hand and will have to bat out of their skins to have any chance in this game. They would need their experienced players to come good and put on a show to try and save this Test match. They have 3 days to bat and against this formidable bowling line-up, if they manage to do it then this Bangladesh side will go down in history. Can they do it? Join us in a while to find out.

Welcome to the coverage of Day 3 of the first Test between India and Bangladesh. With a massive lead of 343 and 3 days of play left in this game, the question on everyone's mind is when will Kohli declare? The hosts have enough runs and more than ample time to take 10 wickets. The way they attacked in the final session would suggest that India might not even bat to start the day. But the hosts might let Bangladesh take the field and demoralise their fragile confidence even further. The visitors will have to bat out of their skins if they are to bow down with some respectability but before that they need to keep their heads strong and not get demotivated if they are asked to bowl today. Only a miracle can see them salvage anything out of this Test. With India in a position to call all the shots in this game, what will their decision be? Join us in a while to find out.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Now then, the question on Day 3 is - When will India declare? Will Kohli decide to do so overnight? All these questions will be answered on Saturday which could also be the last day of this Test. Do join us at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Till then, take care and goodbye!

Mayank Agarwal is down for an interview with Deep Dasgupta. He says that letting go of the fear of failure made him change his mindset and after that, he got hungrier for runs. Adds that there have been times when he didn't get runs so he wants to make most of his batting form by scoring big. Further says that playing his first game in Melbourne was special and helping his side win the game was a great feeling. Adds that the plan was to build partnerships and once that happened, they looked to get quick runs. Says that he backs himself to hit the biggies. Informs that they have not thought about the declaration yet but they are in the driver's seat.

The Bangladesh bowlers gave everything out there but except for Jayed, no other bowler looked threatening. Their spinners were actually played out with a lot of ease. Hasan did take a wicket but he went for almost 5 runs per over. Ebadot bowled a lot of overs but only had one wicket to his name. A very tiring day for them and one which they would like to forget.

Today was all about Agarwal though! The Indian opener is enjoying a golden patch in his career, especially in the first innings of a Test match. He has consistently scored well in the first innings of a Test match but today was something special. The way he attacked, the ease with which he was batting was just brilliant. He was well supported by Rahane and then Jadeja. The former missed out on a well-deserved ton whereas Jadeja has remained unbeaten at the end of the day. Umesh Yadav too enjoyed himself with the bat as he walked out to the middle before Ashwin and hit the ball to all parts of the ground. Overall, they have made the Bangladesh players toil really hard in the field and the visitors will be mentally and physically drained.

WOW! What an entertaining half-hour of play did we witness in the end! Umesh Yadav and Ravindra Jadeja both have a smile as they walk off the field and rightly so. The duo has added 39 in 19 balls and has stretched the lead close to 350. Don't think we need to mention which team is on top, it is quite obvious that when one side scores more than 400 runs in a day, they have to be in the driver's seat.
Full and wide outside off, Yadav goes after it but misses. THAT IS STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Slower one on middle, Jadeja mistimes it down to long on for one.
TOP EDGE, FOUR! Shorter in length and on middle, Jadeja looks to pull but the ball flies off the top edge and over keeper for another boundary. Runs leaking at the moment.
Slower one outside off, this is hit down to long off for one.
Direct hit and Jadeja was a goner! On the body, this is worked towards mid-wicket. They take one, Jadeja wanted a second but is sent back. The fielder throws it at the non-striker's end but misses.
FOUR! Stand and deliver! Jadeja makes room and Jayed bowls a length ball on middle, this is smashed past mid off and a boundary results. 400 runs in the day today, 3rd time India have done so.

FIFTY! 14th one for Jadeja in Tests. He has seriously improved his batting in recent times and he has shown it in this innings. Ravindra gets to the milestone by playing this length ball to the point region. He celebrates it in his traditional way, swinging his bat like a sword.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
LEG BYE! Slower delivery on the pads, Yadav looks to flick it but it goes off the pads towards the leg side for a single.

SIX! Another one! This is carnage going on at the moment. Hossain bowls a short delivery down the leg side, Yadav rocks on his back foot and pulls it towards the fine leg region for a maximum. Marais Erasmus, the umpire goes upstairs to check whether it is a six or a boundary. The replays show that it is the former.

SIX! Umesh Yadav is on fire at the moment in Indore! He moves to 18 off just 6 balls. Full delivery on off, Umesh stands deep in the crease and slams this over the long on region for another maximum. The fielder looked interested for a while but it goes over his head.
Full on middle, Jadeja flicks it to deep mid-wicket and moves to 49 with that single.
FOUR! In the gap and the dressing room is up on its feet! Full and on middle, Yadav heaves it, it goes through mid-wicket and a boundary results.
A slower one outside off, Yadav goes after it but gets an inside edge which goes on the bounce to the keeper.
Goes for another one but this time he mistimes the pull shot over mid-wicket and two is taken.

SIX! This is why he is out there! Yadav is out to entertain the crowd in the last few minutes of play today. Gets off the mark with a biggie. On the pads, Yadav whips it over the backward square leg fence for a biggie.
Good length again, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed towards cover.
Abu Jayed is back on. His figures are 23-3-84-4.
Good length ball on off, Yadav defends it to cover.
Umesh Yadav is the next man in.

OUT! TIMBER! Finally, finally Ebadot Hossain gets his wicket of the innings. Hossain bowls this full on middle, Saha looks to flick it but hits the thigh pad and goes onto hitting the off stump. Hossain does a Cottrell like salute after picking up this wicket,
WIDE! BOUNCER! Hossain bowls this down the leg side, Saha lets it go. The umpire gives it wide for height.
Short ball on off, Saha looks to pull it but it goes off the bottom edge to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Wriddhiman flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes it to cover and crosses over for another single.
Good length ball on off, Saha pushes it to point and takes a single.
Ebadot Hossain is back on! 29-5-98-0 are his figures so far.
Flatter delivery on middle, Saha flicks it to deep square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Nicely played from Saha! Flatter delivery outside off, Saha plays the cut shot to third man to pick up another boundary. India's lead moves to 300 now.
Flighted ball on off, Saha plays it to the leg side.
FOUR! Saha joins the act now! Mehidy bowls a full delivery on off, Saha bends on his knees and sweeps this one through the square leg region for another boundary.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Jadeja punches it to cover and takes another single.
SIX! That is huge! Floated ball on off, Jadeja comes down the track and heaves it over the deep mid-wicket region for a huge maximum.
Misfield! Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover where the fielder fails to stop it and a run is taken.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
On middle, it is flicked to mid on.
Jadeja comes down the track but gets too close to the pitch of the ball and ends up hitting it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, Jadeja manages to keep it out again.
Flatter and on middle, Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
Mahmudullah is back! Change of ends for him.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Flatter delivery on off, Saha guides it with an angled bat towards third man and takes a couple.
BEATEN! Flighted ball outside off, Saha looks to defend it but fails to put any bat on it.
Wriddhiman Saha is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mayank falls after a playing a marathon of a knock. This has been a top knock from the opener and it has put India in a very commanding position. Mehidy bowls a flighted ball on middle, Agarwal plays the slog sweep towards mid-wicket but it goes straight into the hands of Abu Jayed who takes it to his right. A 300 was there for the taking but Mayank was playing for the cause of the team and perishes in doing so. A little too late for Bangladesh as this game has way beyond them to make a comeback. Just as Agarwal walks back to the pavilion, the Bangladesh players shake hands with the Karnataka batsman.

SIX! Another one goes into the stands. Mehidy goes full outside off, Agarwal comes down the track and slams this over the long off region for another maximum. The bat came off the handle but it still has enough to go over the fence.
Flighted ball on middle, Agarwla flicks it to mid-wicket.
Mehidy Hasan is back on.
Short of a length ball outside off, Jadeja punches this off the back foot to cover where the fielder misfields allowing the batsmen to take two.
FOUR! This is absoulte rubbish bowling from Taijul Islam! Bowls another one down the leg side. All Jadeja has to do is to get bat on it which he does. The ball goes to fine leg for another boundary.
Loopy ball on off, Mayank pushes it towards cover and crosses over for an single.
Full delivery on middle, Jadeja flicks it towards the leg side for another single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Jadeja comes down the track and plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor bowling this from Taijul. Bowls this short on pads, Jadeja pulls it to backward square leg for another boundary. Absolute mayhem from these two.
On off, pushed towards mid on.

SIX! Stand and deliver! Mahmudullah tosses this one up on middle, Agarwal stands in his crease and lifts this over the bowler's head for another huge maximum. 100-run partnership is also up between the two.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja punches this off the back foot to cover and crosses over for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Jadeja flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Jadeja these! Flatter delivery down the leg side, Jadeja just helps it on its way to fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted ball outside off, Jadeja defends it to cover and wants the single but is sent back.
On middle, this is kept out.
Flatter and outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Shorter and on middle, Jadeja pushes it to the left of the bowler who gets there quickly.
Jadeja comes down the track but Taijul bowls it short. Jadeja pads it away.
Flatter and on middle, Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
SIX! Jadeja loves the ball turning into him. This one though is pitched right in his zone. Full and on off, Jadeja lifts it with the angle and the turn over the mid-wicket fence. 400 up for India.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! This is a case of another piece of poor fielding. Flighted ball on off, Agarwal drives it to cover where the fielder misfields allowing the ball to go into the fence. The fielder from long off comes across in an attempt to stop the ball but does not reach it in time.
Full delivery on middle, Agarwal drives it straight down the ground and gets to pick another couple as the fielder at long on misfields.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! This timje finds the gap does Agarwal! Mahmudullah tosses this one up outside off, Mayank strides forward and creams the drive through extra cover for a boundary.
Floated ball outside off, Mayank lunges forward and creams this wide of long off for another couple.
Starts with a flatter delivery on off, Agarwal pushes it back to the keeper.
Mahmudullah is on for the first time in this innings.
Tossed up ball on off, Agarwla drives it to long off and takes a single.
Flighted ball on off, Agarwal defends it to cover.

SIX! A flat ojne this time from mayank Agarwal! Taijul tosses this one up on middle, Agarwal puts on his dancing shoes and hammers it straight down the ground for a flat maximum. Reaches his highest score in Tests.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Agarwal pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on off, Agarwal pushes it to cover.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Jadeja pushes it through mid on and takes the single.
The flashlights have come on in the stadium.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes it to cover-point and keeps strike for the next over.
Short delivery on the leg stump line, Mayank pulls it towards fine leg and croses over for another single.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Agarwal flicks it to the leg side.
Another one on a good length on middle, Agarwal pushes it down to mid on.
On a length on off, Agarwal guides this off the back foot to backward point and takes a couple.

FOUR! Short of a length delivery on off, Agarwal looks to pull it but gets cramped for room. He does time it well but the ball has enough to reach the deep mid-wicket fence. The fielder at deep square leg did not even attempt to stop the ball.
Flighted ball on middle, Agarwal flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Low full toss on middle, Jadeja works it to long on and takes a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Ravindra works it to mid-wicket.
Floated ball on middle, Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one on off, Mayank strides forward to defend but it takes the inside edge and the ball goes to mid-wicket. The batters take a single.
Full toss on off, Agarwal drives it to cover for nothing.
Taijul Islam is on now.
One more delivery on a length and around off, blocked.
One more ball outside off, Jadeja does not fiddle with it.
One more delivery outside off, Jadeja lets it go again.
Fuller and on middle, Jadeja strokes it back to the bowler.
This is angled into the body, Agarwal works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Flighted ball on middle, Agarwal flicks it to the leg side for a single.

SIX! Second double century for Mayank Agarwal in Tests! This has been an innings of high class from the Karnataka opener. Since he made his debut in Australia, Mayank has grown in stature ever since. Coming to the ball, it is a flighted ball on middle, Mayank comes down the track and heaves it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. He raises his bat and soaks in the applause from his teammates. Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper is seen signalling from the dressing room to go for the 300. Boy, Bangladesh must be ruing that dropped catch of him on Day 1.
Another flighted ball on middle, Agarwal flicks it to the leg side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Agarwal pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Mayank works it to mid on.
Flatter delivery outside off, Agarwal pushes it to cover.

Drinks! Another hour which has belonged to the hosts. Although they lost the wicket of Rahane early on in the session, Mayank Agarwal and Ravindra Jadeja have motored along nicely to continue building on India's lead. Bangladesh, on the other hand, are going through the motions and in need of some miracle to get back in this game. It is almost impossible for that to happen but anything can happen in cricket.
Low full toss on middle, Agarwal flicks it through mid-wicket and takes a single. 50-run stand comes up between the two.
Short delivery on off, Agarwal rocks on his back foot  and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and picks up a couple. Just five runs away from a wonderful double ton.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal defends it to the off side.

Fullish delivery outside off, Agarwal was in two minds whether to leave this ball or play at it but in the end decides to shoulder arms. Sunny G on air says that this is the line that he should be bowling.
Good length ball on middle, Agarwal defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Brilliantly played from Agarwal! Hossain bowls a short of a length ball outside off, Mayank just stands tall and guides it through backward point for a boundary. Moves into the 190s now.
Ebadot Hossain is back on.
Shorter and on middle, Agarwal pushes it through mid off for one.
This is angled into the pads, Jadeja works it through mid-wicket for one.

A huge appeal but not sure for what. Tha arm ball on middle, Jadeja lunges and keeps it out. the bowler is appealing as he feels it is pad first. nothing from the umpire. Replays though show that the ball did hit the pad first. However, the impact would have been umpire's call so it would have remained not out.
On the pads, Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
On the shorter side and on middle, Agarwall pulls it through mid-wicket for one. 350 up and the lead is now 200.
On the shorter side and on the body, this is pulled through backward square leg for one.
A short one on middle, Agarwal evades it.
Way too wide outside off, it is left alone.
Crisp drive! Fuller and on off, Agarwal creams it but to mid off.
Shorter and outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards point where the fielder dives and saves at least two for his side. Single taken.
On the fuller side, Agarwal opens the face of the bat and guides it through point for one.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
This is fired on the middle pole, Jadeja lunges and keeps it out.
Gives it a nice loop and lands it on middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, gets his line this time. It is kept out.
FOUR! That is a nothing delivery! A hit-me ball. Short and down the leg side, Agarwal pulls it over square leg and gets another boundary.
Flatter and around off, it is angled away from around the wicket. Agarwal looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down towards third man for two.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder comes across to clean it up.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes it to cover.
Jadeja defends this good length ball onto the pitch. Abu runs to collect the ball in an attempt to run Jadeja out but fails to do so. Jayed seems to have hurt his hamstring there.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja looks to flick it but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls to the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flighted ball on off, Jadeja defends this to cover and takes a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Jadeja flicks it to the leg side for nothing.
Mehidy tosses one up again on off, Agarwal looks for another lofted shot but does not time it well. The ball goes to long on and the batters take a single.
SIX! Lovely use of the feet from Agrawal. Mehidy bowls a tossed up ball on off, Mayank dances down the track and slams this over long off for another maximum.
Floated ball on middle and leg, Ravindra flicks it to fine leg and gives Agarwal the strike.
Tossed up ball on middle, Jadeja defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Agarwal flicks it to the leg side. Maiden over from Abu Jayed.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal guides this to gully off the back foot.
Another full one on middle, Agarwal drives but does so uppishly. Luckily for Mayank, the ball falls short of the mid off fielder.
Bowls a full delivery on middle, Agarwal plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery on off, Agarwal defends it to mid off of the back foot.
On a length on off, Agarwal pushes it to cover for nothing.
Full delivery on off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
Floated ball on off, Jadeja prods forward and defends it to cover.
Fullish delivery on middle, Agarwal pushes this through mid on and takes a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Mayank flicks it to square leg.
Floated ball on middle, Agarwal defends it to the leg side.
Tosses this one up on off, Mayank plays it back to the bowler.
Mehidy Hasan is back on. He has bowled 20 overs till now but not yet taken a wicket. His side would love one here.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish delivery outside off, Jadeja has no problems in leaving this alone.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Another full delivery on off, Jadeja defends it to cover.
Fullish delivery on off, Jadeja drives it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is audacious from Agarwal. He stands tall to this short of a length ball outside off and hammers this over cover and picks up another boundary.
Full delivery on the pads, Jadeja flicks it to backward square leg and takes a single.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on off, Jadeja attempts to defend but it goes off the outside edge through gully for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Mayank guides this to third man and takes a single.
Full delivery this time from Hossain, Agarwal drives it beautifully but it hits the boot of Ebadot and the ball rolls to mid off.
Short of a length ball on middle, Agarwal stands tall and pushes it back to the bowler.
Jayed dishes out a full ball outside off, Ravindra does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Mayank punches this off the back foot to cover and crosses over for a single.
Good length ball on middle, MA defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Jadeja gets off the mark by driving this towards mid off.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Full delivery outside the off stump line, Jadeja lets the ball go to the keeper.
Bouncer! Hossain bowls it on the leg stump, Mayank ducks under it.
Short ball outside off, Mayank pushes this towards cover and calls Jadeja for a couple. The fielder comes across and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
FOUR! Hammered! Hossain dishes out a full ball outside off, Mayank lunges and thrashes the ball through the cover region for a boundary.
Another full delivery outside off, Agarwal drives this to cover.
Fullish delivery on middle, Agarwal looks to defend it but it hits the inside edge of the bat and onto the pads. No harm done though.
Good length ball outside off, Mayank shoulders arms to this one.
Another fullish delivery way outside off, Ravindra shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Jadeja lets the ball go to the keeper.
Ravindra Jadeja is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally the partnership is broken and another wicket falls to Abu Jayed. Short of a length outside off, Rahane cuts it uppishly but does not time it well. Unluckily finds Taijul at deep point. Ajinkya unfortunately misses out on a well deserved 100. Has the wicket come too late for Bangladesh though?
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Poor bowling this from Abu Jayed! He bowls a full delivery on the pads, Rahane will not miss out on these and he just flicks it towards fine leg. Ebadot runs across from deep square leg and puts in a dive to stop it but fails to do so. The ball rolls into the fence.
Full delivery outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
Abu Jayed will bowl from the other end.
Another one on a length around off, Mayank opens the face of the bat and guides it to the slip cordon. 2 runs have come off the over.
Good length delivery on off, Agarwal defends it onto the pitch.

Full delivery on middle, Mayank looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge of the bat towards square leg. Mayank wants the second and takes off. Taijul has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Had he hit, it would have been close.
BOUNCER! It is bowled on the leg stump line, Mayank ducks under it.
On a length on off, Mayank defends it to point for nothing.
Ebadot starts with a good length ball way outside off, Agarwal leaves the ball alone.

We are back for the final session! Mayank Agarwal and Ajinkya Rahane make their out to the middle to resume their innings. The Bangladesh players are also making their way out. Ebadot Hossain will start for the hosts. 32 overs remain in the day.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

What a session for India! They are in the driver's seat as the lead is above 150 and they are still a long way from being done. The session started with Agarwal and Rahane continuing from where they left off before the Lunch break. The former got to his ton and the latter to his half ton and are going from strength to strength. Also, they have upped the ante a little. India will probably bat, try and drain Bangladesh mentally and physically before they declare. For Bangladesh, all they can do is to get wickets quickly or just hope the declaration arrives as soon as possible. Stay tuned for the last session.
Good length ball on off, Ajinkya blocks it. That will be Tea on Day 2!
Outside off, Rahane wants to go to Tea unbeaten so he won't even bother playing this. He leaves this one as Australia's Steven Smith.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Full outside off, Rahane drives it to the right of short cover. The fielder there dives and gets his hands to it taking the pace of the ball.
Full and swinging in. Good ball this from Abu. Rahane defends it towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal defends it.
Change of bats for Mayank Agarwal. Maybe this one is to go hammer and tongs. Only time will tell.
Another one down the leg side. Agarwal looks to flick but misses again.
Good length ball on off, Mayank defends it.
Sprays one down the leg side. Agarwal looks to flick but cannot get close to the ball.
Back of a length on middle, Rahane pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal plays it to point for a single.
Ebadot Hossain is back.
Full on off, Ajinkya defends it with proper technique.
Full on off, Ajinkya defends it off the front foot.
Length ball outside off, Ajinkya leaves it alone.
Full on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! The ball races to the fence in a flash. Rahane moves into the 80s and India go past 300 taking their lead over 150. Good length ball outside off, Rahane slashes it through point for a boundary.
Way outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
No Ball! Not an ideal start with the new ball as Jayed oversteps. Full and outside off, Rahane strokes it wide of sweeper cover for two.
New ball taken by the visitors. Abu Jayed to start with it.
The physio is back at work as Mayank Agarwal is being stretched.
On the stumps, MA defends it.

Punched off the back foot by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.

The batsman works it down the leg side.
Shorter on off, Agarwal punches it to the off side for a single.
Flighted on off, Mayank defends it off the front foot.
Short and spinning away, Mayank pushes it with the spin towards point.
Shorter on off, Rahane whips it to long on for a single.

This time flicks it through mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
