FOUR! 150 up for Mayank. This is superb batting! Shorter on  off, Mayank gets on his back foot and pulls it over cow corner to get to his milestone. He is looking unbeatable at the moment. Subdued celebration from the Karnataka boy. His teammates applaud this gem of a knock. He gives a thumbs up to the dressing room and gets back to his work.
Now milks this one to long off for one.
FOUR! This is some absolute masterclass batting against spin. Slightly overpitched on off, Rahane strokes it through mid on and gets a boundary.
Around the pads, MA whips it but finds mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Agarwal pushes it to mid on.

SIX! That was six the moment it left the bat! Brings up the 150-run stand between the duo. Tossed up on middle and off, Agarwal comes down the track and smashes it with sweetness over the long on fence for a biggie.
Flighted on off, Mayank pushes it to mid on.
Shorter off spinner on off, Mayank defends it by getting behind it.
Tossed up on off, Rahane flicks it to the on side for a single.
Floated on off, Mayank dabs it to short third man.
SIX! One of the most toughest shot in the game to play and Mayank plays it with absolute ease. Flighted on off, Mayank comes down the track and goes inside out over extra cover for a maximum.
Floated on off, Mayank looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of his bat behind square on the off side.

Flighted on off, Rahane defends it with ease.

On the stumps, Rahane gets behind the ball and defends.

Floated on off, Mayank defends it to mid on.

The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.

Flighted on off, Ajinkya keeps it out.

The physio is out now, stretching Mayank Agarwal's back. Seems like there is an issue with his lower back.
Floated on off, Agarwal looks to drive but hits it back towards the bowler off the inner half.
FOUR! India changing gears here. Short on middle, Mayank gets on his back foot, uses the depth of the crease really well and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Floated on off, Rahane comes down the track and slashes it towards long on for a single.

FOUR! Up and over! Takes a few steps down the track, converts it into a full toss and lofts it over the mid on fielder and bags another boundary. 250 up for India.
Darts it on the stumps, Agarwal keeps it out.

Mehidy Hasan is back!

Drinks Break! Solid hour for the hosts. They haven't lost a wicket and have scored at a good rate too. The game is slowly slipping away from the visitors and at the moment they seem clueless about what to do. They need someone to step up for them and that to soon. Will that happen? We will have to wait and watch.
Another short ball, Rahane pulls it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Good shot but just a single. Back of a length on off, Agarwal pulls it with authority but there is a man at deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Mayank is such a lovely player of spin bowling. Taijul drags it down, Mayank is quick to get on his back foot and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Good end to the over.
Flighted on off, Mayank finds Mushfiqur at mid on with his glances.

Fifty for Rahane. Ajinkya Rahane has been amongst the runs recently and he has once again played a classy knock here. Full on middle and off, Rahane flicks it through mid-wicket for a single to get to his 21st Test fifty.

Good length ball on off, Rahane punches it through covers and gets a couple as the fielder from sweeper cover cleans it. Gets to 49.
Abu Jayed is back on. The only Bangladesh bowler to get into the wickets column. The keeper is standing up for him now.

HUNDRED FOR MAYANK AGARWAL! This has been a brilliant knock. It has been a fun innings to watch. Third Test hundred in just the 12th innings. Good length ball on the pads, Mayank glances it towards square leg and gets a couple to get to his milestone. He raises his arms and is ecstatic to get to it. He raises his bat and hugs his partner as all his teammates and crowd applaud this glorious knock. He is not just cementing his place in this Test side but he is also becoming Mr. 1st innings man for India.
Wide! But credit to Liton. That had written 4 wides written all over it. Another bouncer. This one is too high. Liton behind the stumps jumps and takes a good one-handed take.
Good idea. Bangs in a bouncer. Agarwal ducks under it.

FOUR! Wow! That is the shot of the day. Full on off, Mayank gets on his front foot and drives it with elegance straight down the ground for a boundary. Moves to 99 and takes his team's total past 200.
FOUR! Slightly short and Rahane gets on his back foot and punches it with power through point for a boundary.
Jinks comes down the track for this one and pushes it back to Mehidy.
Flighted off spinner on off, Ajinkya defends it with a straight bat.
Tossed up on off, Rahane pushes it back to the bowler.

Good shot but cannot go past the fielder. Full on middle and leg, Mayank plays a good looking flick but straight to mid-wicket.
Mayank is in no hurry to get to his century. Length ball outside off, Agarwal says' I am not going to go after it' and leaves it.
Very good ball. Almost a yorker on middle and off, Agarwal manages to flick it to mid-wicket.
Bouncer on off, Rahane pulls it to deep square leg for a single. Gives the strike to Agarwal who is on 95.
No swing. It keeps straight on the fourth stump line. Rahane does not tease it.
Full on off, Rahane pushes it back to the bowler on a bounce. Ebadot stretches out his right hand and saves runs.
On the stumps, Agarwal plants his front foot forward and works it to mid-wicket.
Very short and on the pads, Ajinkya works it through square leg and takes a single.
Very full and on middle, Rahane pushes it to the man at mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
On off, kept out.

Was that a chance? Shorter and on the pads, Rahane looks to pull but it goes off something towards short leg who started running to his right but then realizes the ball is to his left. By the time he tries to adjust it goes past him. Replays though show it was off the pad.
Lovely drive but for no runs! Fuller and on off, Agarwal strokes it to covers.
Shorter and outside off, Agarwal plays it late, he looks to get it past gully but the fielder there dives and stops it.
On the fuller side again, Agarwal looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards mid on. He played that away from the body.
Fuller and on off, Agarwal strokes it nicely but to covers.
Shorter and outside off, Rahane pushes it through covers and takes one.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
Ebadot Hossain to start the second session from the other end.
FOUR! First runs in the session and it is in the form of a boundary! Shorter and on middle, Agarwal goes back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. He is 5 runs away from a ton now.
Down the leg side, Agarwal lets it be.
Shorter and on middle, MA goes back and works it towards square leg. The batters think of a run but then bail out.
Another one on middle, Agarwal works it to the man at mid-wicket.
On middle, Mayank lunges and keeps it out.
Starts off with a very full ball on middle, Agarwal works it to mid-wicket.
We are all set for the action to resume! The Indian batters, Mayank Agarwal and Ajinkya Rahane will continue their innings. Mehidy Hasan to start the proceedings after the break. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Bangladesh bowlers worked hard. Abu Jayed has been the pick of the lot picking up both the wickets of the session to add to his overnight tally of one. The issue for them is that the duo of Rahane and Agarwal are starting to get runs at ease. The other bowlers need to find a way to get into the wickets column and restrict India from getting a massive lead. Can the bowlers find some source of inspiration or will India keep running away with this? Join us at 1210 local (0640 GMT) for the second session of this Test.

Another session that will have India's name all over it. The hosts started the day on a positive note with Pujara taking the charge. He though soon departed after getting to his fifty and then on a rare occasion, the Indian skipper, Virat Kohli departed without troubling the scorers. It looked like Bangladesh might find a way to sneak in this game but then Rahane and Mayank Agarwal joined hands. The duo have added 69 runs and taken India's lead to 38 at Lunch. Agarwal in particular has played another standout innings here and will look to get another ton in the second session.
Shorter in length this time, Rahane stays back again and pushes it back to the bowler. A maiden and the players head towards the pavilion as IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Attacks the stumps once again, Rahane prods forward and blocks it.
Flatter this time and on off, AR is solid in defense.
Once again a loopy ball on off, Rahane keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! Slows it up and lands it on off, it pitches and turns away a little. Rahane prods forward and looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Flatter and on off, Rahane goes back and keeps it out.
One more single as Rahane strokes it to long on.
This time it is a single as this one is eased down to long on.
A loopy delivery on off, Agarwal works it to the right of the bowler who does not stop it. Short mid-wicket gets across and saves a single.
On the pads, Agarwal decides late to sweep it but hits it straight to square leg.
On middle, Agarwal works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
On off, Agarwal lunges and defends it.
Quicker and on off, Rahane keeps it out.
Another shorter in length delivery, Agarwal goes back and pushes it through covers for another single.
Shorter and outside off, Rahane goes back and pushes it through covers for one.
Flatter again and on middle, Rahane stays back and keeps it out easily.
Flatter and on off, the batter goes back and guides it to point.
Loopy ball on off, it is defended.
Loopy ball on middle, this is hit down to long on for one.
Bad bounce! Shorter and on off, Rahane goes back and pushes it towards cover. The ball bounces awkwardly and hits the fielder on the chest. No runs taken.

Well fielded! This is on middle, it turns back in. Agarwal looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards fine leg. The fielder at backward square leg hares after it, slides and saves a run for his side.
Slightly short and on middle, Agarwal goes back and pulls it through mid-wicket for two.
Another delivery on middle, Agarwal works it to mid-wicket.
Good fielding! This is on middle, this pushed back to the right of the bowler who dives and stops it. Saves a run.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, it is kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Driven towards the mid off region. They pick up a single.
On middle, it is kept out.
Rahane has overstretched his right leg while taking a run. The physio has come out to have a check on him.

Short and outside off, Rahane goes back and pushes it through covers. There is a fielder in the deep and a run is taken. Rahane seems to be in pain as he completes that run and straightaway signals the physio to come out.
Fires it on middle, Rahane stays back and pushes it down to long on for one.
FOUR! Lovely shot! A little too full and Rahane makes the bowler pay. He caresses it through the cover region and it races away to the fence.
Floats it up on off, MA eases it down to long on for one.
On the stumps again, Agarwal keeps it out.
Floats it up on off, Agarwal lunges and works it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball around off, Agarwal plays it back to the bowler.

A huge appeal for an LBW and up goes the finger! Mayank can't believe he has been given out. He walks down towards his partner and after a chat reviews. NOT OUT! Replays roll in and they show the ball is going down the leg stump. Excellent use of the review.

Shorter and on middle, Rahane eases it to long on and takes one.

Flighted on off, Agarwal milks it down to long off for a single.

On off, defended with a straight bat by Rahane.

Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

We are all set to begin Day 2! Mayank Agarwal and Cheteshwar Pujara stride out to the middle to resume their innings. The Bangladesh players are also making their way out. Ebadot Hossain will start for the visitors.

Pitch report - Murali Kartik is there for the pitch report. He is joined by Sunil Gavaskar who says the pitch remains good for batting. Adds that there are some footmarks near the short length area and if the faster bowlers bowl here, we might see some uneven bounce today.

After bundling Bangladesh for a mere 150 runs on Day 1, an unbeaten 72-run stand between Mayank Agarwal and Cheteshwar Pujara saw the Indians dominate. The pacers made the ball talk as Shami led the pack with a 3-fer. The visitors removed the in-form Rohit Sharma early with the ball but they could not pick another wicket as both Agarwal and Pujara got themselves in. And, once that happened, runs came thick and fast for the hosts. Mayank Agarwal got a life when Imrul Kayes dropped a sitter in the slips and the opener since then did not allow another opportunity. Pujara, on the other hand, has looked at his fluent best, scoring runs at a brisk pace. Now, how will Day 2 pan out? Indian skipper Virat Kohli had reckoned that the surface will be best for batting from the second day. With 9 wickets intact, Kohli's men would want to post a mountain in front of the visitors to bat  them out and then look to bundle them again. Will they be able to do that or will the Bangladeshi bowlers be able to put the hosts under pressure with quick wickets? We will soon find out. Welcome to our coverage of the second day of this Test match.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

So that is it from the first day of the first Test. India will look to further strengthen their grip on this match while Bangladesh will hope that a new day brings a change in their fortune. They would look to fight back and present a better challenge. The question is can they? Join us on Friday, 15th November for Day 2. The play will begin at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Till then, cheers!

One of the stars with the ball for India, Mohammed Shami is caught down for a chat with Sanjay Manjrekar. Shami says that he looks at the conditions and then decides what line to bowl on this wicket. Says he looks to use the width of the crease well. Adds that he enjoys taking wickets for the team and thinks bowling tight lines and lengths are the key to getting wickets.

A tiring and forgetful day for the visitors. They struggled with the bat and barring the wicket of Rohit Sharma, they have had nothing to cherish with the ball. The bowlers have had to toil hard and with a below-par score on the board that is always a struggle for the bowlers. They though need to keep their focus and come back stronger on Day 2.

So that is it from this game. India continue their dominance with a demolishing win over Bangladesh. Also, they continue their unbeaten run in the ICC World Test Championship. We are not done with the series however as we now move to Kolkata for the first ever Day-Night Test match to be played by India. Kohli and co. will look to convert their red ball dominance into pink ball as well. Bangladesh, on the other hand, will look to put on a better display and stun the home crowd by drawing the series. The historic pink ball Test will begin on Friday, 22nd November. The match will start at 1300 local (0730 GMT). Join us for that one. Till then, cheers!

For his brilliant innings of 243, Mayank Agarwal has been named the Man of the Match. Mayank smiles and says that he hopes that the smile continues for a longer period. Tells he practices but not much as they play the shorter formats as well. Agarwal feels proud to represent India. Says it is great to have someone who wants you to get more runs than himself as Kohli wanted him to get to a double ton when he reached 150 for the first time in Tests. On being asked whether he has had any practice with the pink ball, Mayank informs they had three sessions of practice with Rahul Dravid.

Indian skipper, Virat Kohli says that it has been a clinical performance. Says that they played with 5 batters and it was a very professional performance. On his pace bowling options, Kohli says they are at the top of their game and feels they bowl excellently on any surface. Says that Bumrah is not here at the moment and when he joins the team, it would be more lethal. On the records, Kohli feels that they have not focused on it and are just looking to get the team as high as possible and inspire the upcoming Indian players. Tells when a young guy comes into the team he knows how important it is to get big runs so he just looks to lay the marker so that the new batters can keep their guard and focus on getting the runs while they are in the zones. On playing pink ball cricket next, Kohli tells he is very excited and proud to be the part of the first Indian side to play a Day-Night Test.

Bangladesh skipper, Mominul Haque says that it was difficult as they won the toss and decided to bat first. On the positives, Mominul says that the bowling of Abu Jayed along with the performance of Rahim and Liton are the positives. He feels that it is a challenge for the top order to score some runs and release the pressure on the middle order batsmen. Further adds that he wants to enjoy the Day-Night Test in Kolkata.
No guesses for who the Man of the Match will be but stay tuned for the presentation as we hear from the captains.

Ishant Sharma jokes and says that the other players don't treat him as a senior. Further adds that there is no difference between a senior and a junior as they try to make each other comfortable. Adds that they all enjoy each other's success. Smiles and says that the body feels weak after a certain age but he is enjoying bowling at the moment. On playing with the pink ball in the next Test, he says that he is excited to play that game as the ball does a bit under the lights.

Umesh Yadav says that his parents have got him here as they made him run and practice hard in his childhood and that is what he tries to use here. Adds that if they keep taking wickets, they get to bowl more overs. Says that they like to contribute with the bat as well. Adds that in the last match against South Africa, skipper Kohli told him to go and hit the ball hard and play freely.

Mohammed Shami admits that they get tired but all the fast bowlers try to enjoy themselves as much as possible. Further adds that they also try to push each other for success. On Umesh's batting, Shami jokes that the boundaries are short in India for Umesh's power. On being asked about his secret to good bowling, Shami goes on to say that he has full freedom from the coach and the captain to bowl however he likes and says that he focuses on lines and lengths.
Harsha Bhogle is down for an interview with the impressive pace bowling trio of Mohammed Shami, Umesh Yadav and Ishant Sharma.

With a massive deficit, Bangladesh needed their openers to fight it out but the opening pair of Kayes and Shadman failed to do that and were unable to hang out there for long. Just like the first innings, the top order did not put up a fight and for a moment it looked like they would struggle to get into the second session with any mainstay batters. However, Mushfiqur Rahim hung around with Mahmudullah. The latter though could not fight for long. Liton and Rahim then counter-attacked the Indian bowlers. Mushfiqur put up a fight with Mehidy Hasan but the task in hand was too much and Rahim's fighting knock was not enough for Bangladesh to avoid an innings defeat.

After deciding to declare with an overnight lead of 343 runs which they gained courtesy of a brilliant 243-run knock from Mayank Agarwal along with vital knocks from Rahane and Jadeja, the hosts started off with the ball in magnificent fashion. The opening bowling pair of Umesh Yadav and Ishant Sharma got rid of the Bangladesh openers. Shami then joined the party and what has become a norm, he was the pick of the bowlers in the second innings. Mohammed Shami ended up with 4 wickets. Ashwin too was once again amongst the wickets as he picked up 3. Umesh and Ishant had 2 and 1 respectively. All-in-all, India were once again superb with the cherry in hand.

Comfortable win for India and they continue their dominance at home in the longest format of the game. They look unbeatable at the moment, especially in their own backyard. A win by an innings and 130 runs. That is a huge margin. No contest this really. It has been a landslide victory.

Drinks Break! Finally a passage of play which the visitors have enjoyed. With nothing to lose, Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das have changed their approach and have gone attacking. They are taking on the attack but they will need to carry this on for a long, long time to get close to India's total. The hosts are still leaps and bounds ahead in this game and would not mind this a bit. They though would look to wrap this game up before the 60th over to not have any points reduced.

We are back for the second session! This one might be just the last session of the game as the hosts are just 6 wickets away. Mushfiqur Rahim and Mahmudullah stride out to the middle to resume the innings. The Indian players are also making their way out. Mohammed Shami will start the proceedings after the break.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

The visitors though have yet again been miserable with the bat after a poor showing in the first innings. They did not have any clue of where the ball was swinging and are now looking at a humiliating loss. They have the experienced duo of Mushfiqur Rahim and Mahmudullah at the crease and they will hope that they can bat for as long as possible to delay the inevitable. Will the second session be the final one of this game? Join us in a while to find out.

22 overs only were only bowled in this session but India will be mightily pleased with this session. They have dominated another one in this game. They have gone onto pick the top 4 wickets of the visitors and now are just six wickets away from a victory. Brilliant opening burst from the Indian seamers broke the back of the Bangladesh batters and when they return from the break they would look to continue the good work and finish the game on this day itself.

Umesh dishes out another full delivery on off, Haque looks to work it to the leg side again. The ball takes the inside edge of the bat and rolls to square leg.
Full delivery on off swinging into the batsman. Mominul looks to flick but it goes off the inside half of the bat through square leg. The batters take a couple.
The new man in is Mohammad Mithun.

OUT! Bowled! Right through the gate of bat and pad. A fast bowler's delight. India dominating. This is brilliant bowling from Ishant. Length ball pitching on off, Ishant makes the ball jag back in. Shadman looks to push it straight but the ball sneaks right through his bat and pad and goes onto hit middle and leg. This Indian side is lethal with the cherry in the hand and today has not been any different so far. Bangladesh two down and the trail is a massive 327.
Fuller on the stumps, Islam defends it off the front foot.

In the air and taken...but it came off the pads. Good length ball that comes in. Shadman looks to flick but misses. The ball lobs to gully off the pads and Jadeja takes it. There is a stifled appeal but it is turned down as the ball came off the pads. Harsha Bhogle on air, gets excited thinking it came off the bat but it wasn't.
Full and coming in on off, Shadman keeps his eyes on the ball and defends right unedr his eye line.
Full on middle and leg, Shadman flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Good length ball shaping away from outside off, Shadman leaves it alone.
Another good length ball outside off swinging into the batsman, Haque lets the ball go to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Poor review this from India! It is not going above the stumps but it is certainly missing the off stump. Good length ball outside off swinging into the batsman, Mominul decides to leave it but the ball brushes his pad and gos to the keeper. Yadav appeals for a LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Yadav is convinced that it is out and forces Kohli to go for the review. The Ultra Edge then rolls in and it shows no bat. The Ball Tracker shows that the ball was going on to miss the off stump. India have lost their first review here courtesy of a poor decision from the Indian skipper.

Review time. It is for an LBW and it is the skipper, Mominul Haque who is the man in question. The impact looks outside but he has not played any shot so the impact does not matter. The question is whether it is hitting the stumps or going over?
Good length ball outside off, Mominul shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! A poor ball this from Umesh! Bowls it a bit too full and wide outside off, Mominul prods forward and drives it through point for a boundary. Gets off the mark with that.
Full delivery outside off, Mominul lets the ball go to the keeper.
Bangladesh skipper, Mominul Haque is the new man in.

OUT! TIMBER! What a ball from Umesh to castle Imrul Kayes! This is top class stuff from the Indian pacer. Full delivery on off swinging into the batsman. Kayes looks to drive it but it goes off the inside edge and uproots the leg stump off the ground. Another early setback for the visitors.
Back of a length delivery on off, Shadman defends it of the back foot to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Shadman looks to work it to the leg side but goes off the leading edge to cover.
On a length on off coming into the batsman. Kayes looks to flick but it goes off the inside half through square leg and takes a single.
BEATEN! Another good delivery from Ishant! Full delivery outside off, Imrul looks to defend from inside the crease but fails to make any connection to it.
Good length ball outside off, Kayes plays inside the line and lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Beautiful piece of bowling this from Sharma! Bowls a full delivery in the channel, Kayes looks to defend but it goes past the bat and into the mitts of the keeper.
That took off from a good length area. Umesh bowls it outside off, Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Islam attempts to defend but it goes off the outside edge and rolls to gully.
Good length ball on middle, Islam defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Kayes works it towards square leg and takes a single.

Ohh! Good length ball down the leg side, Kayes looks to work it towards the leg side off the back foot. The ball brushes the thigh pad and goes to the keeper. There is an appeal for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
Full delivery down the leg side, Kayes looks to flick it but misses it altogether.
There is a slight halt in play. There are some sightscren issues.
Another full delivery outside off tempting Shadman to drive but he shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery around off swinging away from the batsman. Shadman knows where his off stump is and makes a good leave.
Good length ball outside off, Shadman does not fiddle with it and lets the ball pass through to Saha.
On a length on middle and leg, Shadman  blocks it off the back foot to mid off.
Another full delivery on middle, Islam pushes it back to the bowler.
Sharma comes around the wicket and bowls a full delivery outside off, Shadman shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery on off, Kayes defends it to the off side.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Kayes flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Well played that from Imrul Kayes! Gets off the mark with a boundary. Umesh bowls a half volley outside off, Kayes leans forward and creams the drive through cover for the first boundary of the game.
Good length ball on off, Kayes punches it to cover off the back foot.
On a length on middle with a little swing on it. Kayes works it to mid-wicket.
Starts with a good length ball on the pads, Shadman works it to fine leg and crosses over for a single.
Umesh Yadav will share the new ball from the other end.

Bangladesh get their scoreboard ticking. Full on off, Shadman drives it straight. He does not get it right from the meat. Shami goes after the ball and cleans it up before the ropes. The batsmen come back for the third. Shadman will keep the strike.
Back of a length on off, Shadman defends it by getting behind the line of the delivery.
Another good movement for Ishant. It is outside off and moves away, Shadman looks to defend but gets beaten.
Targets the stump now. It is on middle and leg, Shadman looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Ishant comes closer to the off pole and almost finds the outside edge. It is on a length around off, in the channel of uncertainty. Shadman looks to defend but gets beaten.
Ishant starts with a good length ball moving away from the southpaw. Shadman keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone.
